AGENT B: JUSTIFICATION GENERATOR AGENT
Purpose: Convert informal, casual employee messages into formal, professional language.
         Also generates policy-aligned justifications.
Workflow:
1. Receive raw informal text from employee
2. Detect language tone (casual, semi-formal, formal)
3. If casual/semi-formal → rewrite to formal professional tone
4. Show side-by-side comparison to employee: "Here's your message, professionally rephrased"
5. Employee confirms → formal version used for the request
System prompt: "You are a professional language assistant. Convert informal workplace
  messages into clear, formal, professional language. Maintain all factual content.
  Do not add or remove information. Use respectful, corporate-appropriate tone."
Token budget per conversion: ~200 tokens

AGENT C: COUNSELLING AGENT (Emotional & Mental Support)
Purpose: Provide empathetic AI-based emotional and mental health support.
Sub-types (each with tailored prompts):
  - Emotional Support Agent: For stress, anxiety, sadness, overwhelm
  - Mental Wellness Agent: Mindfulness exercises, breathing techniques, grounding
  - Workplace Conflict Agent: Advice on handling workplace interpersonal issues
  - Grief Support Agent: Compassionate support for loss and bereavement
  - Anxiety Management Agent: CBT-based techniques, worry journaling
  - Depression Screening Agent: PHQ-9 style screening (refers to professional if needed)
Safety: Always includes disclaimer — "I'm an AI assistant, not a licensed therapist. 
  If you're in crisis, please contact [emergency helpline numbers]."
Escalation: If crisis keywords detected (self-harm, suicide) → immediately show
  emergency helpline numbers + offer to connect with HR confidentially.
Session tracking: Each counselling session saved to counselling_sessions table.

AGENT D: BURNOUT DETECTION AGENT
Purpose: Proactively detect employee burnout risk.
Inputs monitored (with employee consent):
1. Stressful language in messages — NLP sentiment analysis on request descriptions
   (keywords: "exhausted", "overwhelmed", "can't cope", "breaking point", etc.)
2. Frequent late work hours — login/activity timestamps showing work after 8PM
3. Multiple rejected flexibility requests — pattern of denied WFH/shift change requests
4. Declining wellbeing scores — from wellbeing_tracker data
Scoring:
  - Each indicator scored 0-1
  - Weighted average: language(0.3) + late_hours(0.25) + rejections(0.25) + wellbeing(0.2)
  - Risk levels: Low (<0.3), Moderate (0.3-0.5), High (0.5-0.7), Critical (>0.7)
Actions:
  - Moderate: Kira gently suggests break, wellbeing resources
  - High: Kira recommends counselling session, notifies HR (anonymized)
  - Critical: Alert HR + supervisor with recommended interventions

AGENT E: POSH / HARASSMENT AGENT (Anonymous)
Purpose: Safe, anonymous reporting of workplace harassment per POSH Act compliance.
Workflow:
1. Employee selects "Report Harassment" → enters anonymous mode
2. NO identifying information stored — reporter_hash generated from salted hash
3. Employee describes incident through guided questions (Kira asks sensitively)
4. Details stored in harassment_reports table (encrypted at rest)
5. ONLY assigned HR personnel can view report details
6. AI analyzes for POSH Act applicability and severity
7. POSH analysis stored in posh_analysis_logs
Privacy guarantees:
  - No user_id stored in harassment_reports — only reporter_hash
  - Manager CANNOT see reports — HR only
  - All detail fields encrypted using AES-256
  - Audit logs for harassment table access (who viewed, when)
  - Anonymous report ID provided to reporter for status tracking

AGENT F: SHIFT SAFETY AGENT
Purpose: Evaluate shift schedules to ensure safety for women employees.
Safety evaluation criteria:
1. Late night shifts (after 8PM) — flag, require transport arrangement
2. Isolated location shifts — require buddy system
3. Commute safety based on shift end time
4. Consecutive night shifts — fatigue risk
5. Lone working scenarios — must have check-in protocol
Actions:
  - Score each shift 0-100 for safety
  - Shifts scoring < 60: auto-flag, require manager justification
  - Shifts scoring < 40: block unless transport + buddy arranged
  - Generate safety notes and recommendations
  - Suggest alternative shift arrangements if unsafe

AGENT G: MATERNITY RETURN AGENT (Smart Return-to-Work Support)
Purpose: Support women returning to work after maternity leave.
