PART 8 — AUTHENTICATION & SECURITY
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

AUTHENTICATION:
- Registration: email verified via OTP email before account activation
- Login: email + password → returns JWT access_token (15 min) + refresh_token (7 days, httpOnly cookie)
- Refresh flow: silent token refresh via axios interceptor before expiry
- RBAC (Role-Based Access Control):
  * employee: can create/view own requests, chat with Kira, use all personal assistants,
              view own dashboard, track wellbeing, access counselling, report harassment (anon)
  * supervisor: can view assigned approvals + employee data in their team + shift scheduling
  * hr: can view all requests across org + analytics + harassment reports (ONLY role with access)
        + wellbeing analytics dashboard + burnout indicators
  * admin: full access + user management + policy document management (upload/update/archive)
              + system configuration + ChromaDB re-ingestion

SESSION MANAGEMENT:
- Redis stores session with TTL = 10 minutes (reset on every API call)
- Frontend tracks last interaction time via mousemove/keydown/click events
- At 9 minutes: Kira appears with warning: "You've been inactive for a while. 
  I'll need to log you out in 1 minute for your security. Still there?"
- At 10 minutes: automatic logout → JWT invalidated → redirect to login with message
- "You were automatically logged out to keep your account secure. Welcome back when ready! 💜"

SECURITY STANDARDS (OWASP Top 10 compliance):
- All inputs: Pydantic validation (backend) + Zod schema validation (frontend)
- SQL injection: SQLAlchemy ORM with parameterized queries only
- XSS: React DOM escaping + Content-Security-Policy header
- CSRF: SameSite=Strict on refresh token cookie + CSRF token for mutations
- Rate limiting: slowapi on login endpoint (5 attempts per minute per IP)
- Account lockout: after 5 failed logins → lock 15 minutes → notify user via email
- HTTPS enforced (redirect HTTP → HTTPS)
- Passwords: bcrypt with cost factor 12
- Sensitive fields (justification, harassment reports) encrypted at rest (AES-256 via SQLCipher or app-level encryption)
- Harassment reports: additional encryption layer, access restricted to HR role only
- Audit log: every state change on requests logged to audit_logs table
- Harassment table access logged separately (who accessed, when, IP)
- No PII in frontend logs (mask email, employee ID in Sentry)
- CORS: whitelist frontend origin only
- Security headers: X-Frame-Options DENY, X-Content-Type-Options nosniff, HSTS

