AUTO-APPROVAL FOR EMERGENCY REQUESTS:

Workflow:
1. Employee raises an emergency flexibility request (urgency_level = "emergency")
2. Employee uploads a supporting document (medical certificate, legal notice, etc.)
3. POLICY CHECKER AGENT (Agent N) validates the document:
   a. Extracts text from uploaded document (PDF/image via OCR)
   b. Queries ChromaDB for relevant policy requirements
   c. LLM evaluates: "Does this document meet the requirements specified in 
      the company policy for emergency {request_type}?"
   d. Returns: VALID / INVALID with detailed reasoning
4. If VALID:
   - Request marked: is_emergency=True, document_verified_by_rag=True, 
     auto_approval_eligible=True
   - auto_approval_deadline set to: submitted_at + 48 hours (configurable)
   - Supervisor and HR notified with "URGENT" flag and auto-approval countdown
5. If manager/HR approves before deadline → normal approval flow
6. If NO decision within 48 hours AND document is valid:
   - System auto-approves the request
   - Status set to 'auto_approved'
   - Email E9 sent to employee (confirmation), supervisor (notification), HR (audit)
   - Full audit trail logged: "Auto-approved due to valid supporting document 
     and SLA breach. Document verified against policy: [policy_code]"
7. If INVALID document:
   - Employee notified: "Your document doesn't meet policy requirements. 
     Please upload a valid document or contact HR."
   - Normal approval timeline applies (7 days)

SAFEGUARDS:
- Only emergency requests are eligible for auto-approval (not regular WFH/shift)
- Document MUST pass RAG policy verification — no auto-approval without valid doc
- Admin can configure auto_approval_hours (default: 48)
- All auto-approvals are flagged in audit_logs and analytics
- HR can review and override auto-approvals retroactively if needed

ADMIN POLICY DOCUMENT MANAGEMENT:

Endpoints:
  POST   /api/admin/policies/upload    — Upload new policy document
  GET    /api/admin/policies           — List all policies
  GET    /api/admin/policies/{id}      — View policy details
  PUT    /api/admin/policies/{id}      — Update policy metadata
  DELETE /api/admin/policies/{id}      — Archive policy (soft delete)
  POST   /api/admin/policies/reingest  — Re-ingest all active policies into ChromaDB

Upload workflow:
1. Admin uploads PDF/DOCX/TXT file via the Policy Management page
2. Server saves file to data/policies/ directory
3. Text extracted from document
4. Text split into chunks (LangChain RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter, 500 tokens, 50 overlap)
5. Chunks embedded and stored in ChromaDB with metadata (policy_code, category, version)
6. Policy record created in policies table
7. Confirmation: "Policy uploaded and indexed successfully. 
   RAG retrieval is now updated."

Update workflow:
1. Admin uploads new version of existing policy
2. Old version archived (is_active=False)
3. New version ingested into ChromaDB (old embeddings replaced)
4. Version number auto-incremented
5. All future RAG queries use the latest version

